Task: Implement settings controls in LVGL UI

Summary:
- Added a third 'Settings' tab to the LVGL Tabview in src/ui.cpp with a side-by-side landscape columns layout.
- Integrated switches for temperature unit (C/F) and Auto Light (LDR auto-brightness toggle), a manual brightness slider, and timezone offset buttons.
- Configured callbacks to update SettingsManager in real-time and trigger notification flags.
- Updated main.cpp loop to react to settings changes immediately (forcing weather refetches, updating backlight PWM, and reconfiguring NTP timezone).
- Replaced compile-time UNIT_SYSTEM checks with runtime checks in weather_client.cpp and ui.cpp.
- Verified compilation and test runs successfully on all modules.

Files:
- src/ui.cpp
- include/ui.h
- src/weather_client.cpp
- tests/mocks/mocks.cpp
- tests/test_settings/test_settings.cpp
- src/main.cpp

Why: Completes the integration of UI controls and settings state, providing immediate visual updates and hardware changes on the CYD board when settings are interacted with.
